  "text": "The etcd-io/etcd repository implements comprehensive client-side retry and timeout policy through several coordinated components:\n\n## 1. Retry Interceptor (client/v3/retry_interceptor.go)\nThe core retry logic is implemented via two gRPC client interceptors:\n- `unaryClientInterceptor`: Handles retry for unary RPC calls (Put, Get, Delete, Txn). It supports configurable maximum retries (defaultUnaryMaxRetries = 100), backoff with jitter, and distinguishes between mutable and immutable operations.\n- `streamClientInterceptor`: Handles retry for server-side streaming calls. It buffers messages and can reestablish streams on failure. By default, stream retry is disabled (withMax(0)) for safety.\n- Both interceptors implement exponential backoff via `waitRetryBackoff` and use `backoffLinearWithJitter` for configurable backoff.\n\n## 2. Retry Policy Determination (client/v3/retry.go)\nRetry safety is determined based on operation type and error code:\n- `isSafeRetryImmutableRPC`: Read operations (Range/Get) can be retried on any transient error (codes.Unavailable). Immutable operations are idempotent.\n- `isSafeRetryMutableRPC`: Write operations (Put, Delete, Txn) can only be retried when no connection is available (\"there is no address available\"). This preserves write-at-most-once semantics.\n- Dedicated retry clients wrap protocol buffer clients: `RetryKVClient`, `RetryLeaseClient`, `RetryClusterClient`, `RetryMaintenanceClient`, and `RetryAuthClient`.\n\n## 3. Client Connection and Health Check (client/v3/client.go)\nThe client initialization flow establishes connections with health verification:\n- `New()` → `newClient()` → `dialWithBalancer()` → `dial()` creates the connection\n- `dialSetupOpts()` configures interceptors, keepalive parameters, and TLS credentials\n- `waitForConnection()` performs health check using gRPC's Health Check API after dialing within the DialTimeout. It disables retry (withMax(0)) to avoid unnecessary delays.\n- `roundRobinQuorumBackoff()` implements quorum-aware backoff: waits between attempts after cycling through all endpoints\n- DialTimeout bounds the initial connection establishment time\n\n## 4. Endpoint Balancing and Health Management (client/v3/internal/resolver/resolver.go)\nThe resolver manages endpoint load balancing:\n- `EtcdManualResolver`: Manual resolver with round-robin policy configured via gRPC service config\n- `SetEndpoints()` and `updateState()` dynamically update available endpoints and propagate changes to the gRPC ClientConn\n- Integrates with gRPC's resolver interface for proper endpoint selection across requests\n\n## 5. KV Operations (client/v3/kv.go)\nKV client wraps the protocol buffer KVClient with call options and error handling:\n- Implements Put, Get, Delete, Txn operations with `ContextError` wrapper\n- Calls go through the retry interceptor configured with default call options\n- Timeout enforcement via context.Context passed from caller\n\n## 6. Watch Implementation (client/v3/watch.go)\nWatch provides long-lived streaming with resilience:\n- `watcher` creates multiple `watchGRPCStream` objects for different contexts\n- `watchGRPCStream` manages a single gRPC Watch stream with reconnection logic:\n  - Maintains `substreams` map for individual watchers\n  - `respc` channel receives watch responses\n  - `errc` channel receives stream errors triggering reconnection\n  - Implements resuming logic via `resumec` signal\n- Watch respects caller-provided context but creates an internal `valCtx` that never closes to allow indefinite streaming\n- Handles server-side cancellation and compaction errors\n- Uses stream interceptor with retry disabled by default, but individual watch streams handle reconnection internally\n\n## 7. Lease Implementation (client/v3/lease.go)\nLease management with automatic keep-alive:\n- `lessor` implements keep-alive with configurable `firstKeepAliveTimeout` (defaults to 5 seconds)\n- `KeepAlive()` initiates long-lived stream for lease renewal\n- `KeepAliveOnce()` performs single renewal with retry support\n- `stream` multiplexes multiple lease keep-alives over one gRPC stream\n- Keep-alive deadline management prevents expiration during intervals\n- Uses `WithRequireLeader` context to prevent split-brain scenarios\n\n## 8. Configuration and Options (client/v3/config.go, client/v3/options.go)\nConfigurable retry and timeout behavior:\n- Config fields: `DialTimeout`, `DialKeepAliveTime`, `DialKeepAliveTimeout`, `MaxUnaryRetries`, `BackoffWaitBetween`, `BackoffJitterFraction`\n- Default options in options.go:\n  - `defaultUnaryMaxRetries = 100`: Max retries for unary calls\n  - `defaultBackoffWaitBetween = 25ms`: Wait between retries\n  - `defaultBackoffJitterFraction = 0.10`: 10% jitter\n  - `defaultWaitForReady = true`: Wait for server readiness\n- DialTimeout bounds connection setup\n- MaxCallSendMsgSize and MaxCallRecvMsgSize configure message size limits\n\n## 9. Error Handling and Timeout Enforcement\nUniform error handling across all operations:\n- `ContextError()` converts gRPC errors to etcd errors and respects context cancellation\n- `isHaltErr()` detects non-recoverable errors (returns false only for codes.Unavailable and codes.Internal)\n- `isUnavailableErr()` detects transient connection errors\n- All KV, Watch, and Lease operations apply `ContextError` wrapping\n- Timeout is enforced via context.Context: caller specifies timeout, interceptor respects it\n\nThe implementation ensures:\n1. **Write safety**: Mutable operations retry only when no endpoints are reachable\n2. **Read efficiency**: Immutable operations retry aggressively on any transient error\n3. **Connection health**: Keepalive and health checks maintain connection quality\n4. **Endpoint diversity**: Round-robin with quorum-aware backoff prevents thundering herd\n5. **Long-lived streams**: Watch and Lease support indefinite operation with internal reconnection\n"}
